1: Stella tells the party all she knows about the abyss and the Overlords. After hearing her out, the party enlist Mal Lelucia's aid in heading to the land of the Sheephirds.
4: Alk asks Mal Lelucia about the origins of the Sheephirds. Hearing the legends, the group decides that the fastest way forward would be to speak with the Sheephird Elder directly.

3: To Make a Deal with Dul

The new Elder of the Sheephirds, Dul Kugala, seeks the help of the party for a particular mission. Alongside Zekhel, a member of the Guild Knights, they head to a settlement in the outskirts of Palpebra.

The fierce warrior Memram pursues the party, who attempts to kidnap one of her comrades. Much to her surprise, however, she finds that the group are the legendary heroes who defeated the Lord of Shadow.

1: The group, having failed to negotiate the Vesta's withdrawal from the region, head to the Kaleidoscope via one of its narrow branching paths.
Zekhel observes Memram in a ritual to summon her people, and decides that she poses a danger to Palpebra and must be expelled. Just then, a Purger appears during a distortion.
3: Nova reveals his relationship with the Vesta, and warns the party that if the abyss continues to expand unabated, their world too would become a target for the Purgers.
With negotiations between the Guild and the Vesta having reached an impasse, Alk tries thinking about the problem from a different perspective.

1: After ironing out the details of his secret plan with Zekhel, Alk dives into the Rift alongside Memram.
By using two Star Relics—his and Nova's swords—Alk attempts to rescue the remaining stranded Vesta. A Purger, however, stands in their way again.
Purgers descend from the opening Stella and Alk created by connecting worlds. The full might of Palpebra—including the Guild Knights and adventurers on an "emergency quest"—meets them in battle.
The Vesta choose to live among the Gargans, while Dul Kugala is welcomed to Starview Village. Zekhel offers some advice to the group, while Nova assesses the situation.
2: Nova shares information about his life, as well as a way to meet the Overlords. He and Alk bond over shared guilt, and the two declare each other partners in crime. Shortly after, Nova leaves Starview.

1: Alk wakes, still heavily injured. He learns of Shakari's death, but has little time to mourn—Stella and Lilith get separated from the party, and it's a race against the clock to find them before the Lord of Shadow's forces do.

Reminded of her lost daughters, a fiend named Marly shelters Stella and Lilith. Meanwhile, Adjudicus explains his cause: the fiends seek to secure a better home in the overworld—which the Lord of Shadow is wantonly destroying.
4: A fiend catches the scent of humans on Marly, who rushes to evacuate Stella and Lilith before they meet the same fate as her daughters. En route, the girls encounter Ilbis. The ensuing commotion alerts the rest of the party, who begin fighting their way over to help.

1: Alk wastes precious time subduing foes instead of killing them, prompting Adjudicus to give him a harsh reality check. Meanwhile, Stella and Lilith are backed to the edge of a cliff, and dive into the river below. Adjudicus and Estariel fly over to collect them, then embark for the fiend rebels' keep.

Reunited, the party discuss commandeering the source of Doomsday Lances—the Doomsday Spire. While Stella's power is required, Light insists that Alk stay behind for his safety. Afterwards, Lilith and Alk discuss the gap between their mentors' abilities and their own.
2: Lilith meets with the fiend rebels, who refuse to ally themselves with a human. Their leader, Adjudicus, is more pragmatic. When Lilith presents the Mark of Rustamov for leverage, he accepts her aid for the attack on the Doomsday Spire.

3: Estariel reveals that she and Adjudicus have established a pact to take down the Lord of Shadow, and asks Lilith what mankind's response will be. Lilith affirms her determination to fight on, and to become whatever her people need.

Despite being subjected to a transformation experiment, Marly somehow avoids becoming a monstrous daemon. Ilbis, learning of Adjudicus's betrayal, is further incensed, and asks for a new test subject to be brought out. Meanwhile, the party is informed that they will need to obtain a special weapon that acts as the core of the Doomsday Spire to gain control of the Doomsday Lances on the surface.

4: The party arrives at the location of the Antipode Lance to find a wounded Marly. Ilbis then appears, bringing with him an unexpected guest—Camir, the Lord of the Oasis. The two use the power of the curse to fuse together into a vile monstrosity.

2: The daemon senses Stella's attempts to cut off its regeneration abilities and tries to crush her, only to be thwarted by Lilith. Stella then dispels the barrier around the Antipode Lance, allowing Adjudicus to use it to slay the daemon, ridding the world of Ilbis—and the former Lord of the Oasis.
3: Adjudicus uses the Lance to rejoin the surface to Pandemonium. He then proclaims he will descend into the rift to sever the source of the Lord of Shadow's immortality. Lilith leaves Estariel in charge of matters on the surface before heading below with the others. Marly comes to see them off, imploring them to come back alive.

4: The party comes across the final World Flipper, and Stella succeeds in synchronizing with it. Light begins to glow, but ultimately fails to regain his original form. Adjudicus discusses the fate of Pandemonium, when suddenly the Lord of Shadow himself makes an appearance. Adjudicus swears that he will usurp the Dark Throne and challenges Oghir to a battle.

2: Adjudicus, despite his fervent wishes to secure a future for his people, falters and loses the power of the curse. In his place, Lilith takes up the Antipode Lance, but is overwhelmed by the voices of the spiteful dead. Amidst the chaos, the Lord of Shadow lets loose his formidable Curse Savior attack—only to have it intercepted by Light, risking his life to save his comrades.
3: As Light attempts to hold back the Lord of Shadow's attack, Alk jumps in to help. Under immense pain from the attack, Alk reveals his thoughts to his dear friend. As if reacting to his emotions, the Mark of Rustamov activates, deflecting Oghir's attack. Stella and Lilith use the Antipode Lance to channel the voices of the dead, allowing Light to hear them. Pressed onward by the spirit of Shakari, Light at long last regains the power of the champion.

2: The champion Light has regained his power—albeit only temporarily—and continues his battle with his nemesis. Cooperating with the others, they manage to deal a lethal blow to the Lord of Shadow. Stella's doppelganger rushes to the scene, only to be forcibly sent away by Oghir. Ilbis and Oghir share one final embrace, as Doomsday Lances begin to fill the area. The party hurriedly escapes from the abyss. Meanwhile, a dark dragon's mark begins to glow above the head of the melting Lord of Shadow.

3: Nimbus hears a voice that allows him to lead everyone out of the abyss, where they regroup with Estariel. They find that a massive Doomsday Spire has pierced through the world. Estariel takes the Mark of Rustamov and uses it to grant the party incredible power, which they use to fly to the top of the spire. There, an abomination consisting of countless daemon souls is forming. Now a heinous creature filled only with loathing, the Lord of Shadow stands before the party, challenging them to one final fight.

2: Oghir shares some parting words with Adjudicus and turns to ash, fading away. Lilith senses a presence in the area and turns around to find the figure of Shakari standing there. The two express their feelings to each other, and Shakari tells Lilith how much she loves her before finally departing. Lilith joins the rest of the party and walks on to her bright new future.
3: Lilith, Estariel, and Adjudicus declare the signing of a peace pact between men, elves, and fiends. Alk tells Lilith about the mysteries surrounding his own past, and how he hopes to one day solve them. The group sets off alongside Alk to help him find his home and regain his memories.

1: Stella's doppelganger appears in front of the party, just as the world begins to shake. Doppelganger Stella begins to speak of the rejoining of the seven worlds, and manages to partially stir some of Stella's lost memory. Doppelganger Stella then accuses the party of having "doomed" the world, and swears she will continue the work the Lord of Shadow left unfinished. She reveals her true name: Leve. Then, all World Flippers begin to suddenly resonate, and space itself is rent apart. The merging of worlds has begun.
2: A massive angel-like being descends from the skies and begins to attack. Alk and co. head to the World Flipper in an effort to stop these creatures. After receiving instructions from a mysterious entity known as Nova, Stella is able to successfully stop the creatures' attack.
3: After waking up, Stella finds that her memories have returned. She begins to speak of the Overlords, the rules they set in place, and the real role of the champion. Feeling responsible for this, she decides to set out alone, but Alk and co. find her before she departs, insisting that they go on this journey together. After saying goodbye to Lilith, the group returns to Starview Village to prepare for their new adventure.

1: Alk and co. alight on a barren, frigid world. There, among the rocks and snowdrifts, Light makes a startling discovery.

Alk and co. arrive at the Dark Keep, where Light faced off against the Lord of Shadow. Upon learning that the crumbling fortress has been abandoned, they decide to cross over the mountains and return with Light to the royal capital of Excelion.

2: Alk and co. make it to the grand city of Excelion, only to find it in ruins. Among the rubble, they meet a powerful fire mage who attacks Stella on sight, calling her the Harbinger of Death.

1: Light recognizes the mage as his old compatriot Shakari. She is overcome by indignation when he reveals himself, divulging that in the fifty years since the disappearance of the champion, the kingdom fell, the cleric Joshua died, and the royal family all but perished, with Lilith, Princess Lily's granddaughter, being the sole survivor.

2: Alk's party, Shakari, and a band of refugees are making ready to seek out the Resistance when a woman recognizes Stella as the Harbinger of Death. However, before the refugees can drive her away, a giant lance bursts through the ground and a fiend named Ilbis descends upon the group.

1: Alk and co. defend the refugees from Ilbis and win Shakari's trust. Though she still refuses to believe in Light, she agrees to take the companions to meet Lilith and the Resistance, a force composed of warriors from multiple worlds.

Alk prepares a warm meal to hearten the displaced peoples of Excelion, which prompts Shakari to observe that the battlefield is no place for a heart as gentle as his. But when Alk refuses to back down, the mage sees that he is a kindred spirit to the Princess Lilith.

Shakari leads the party to the gates of the Resistance, where she introduces Alk and his friends from Starview as allies. Despite objections from the other commanders, Lilith welcome refugees and travelers alike into their headquarters.

Alk and co. learn that the World Flipper is hidden beneath Castle Excelion, which has fallen into enemy hands. In order to retake it, they join Lilith and Shakari in a clandestine mission to negotiate an alliance with elves living in the Silver Woods.

Lilith brings her companions to the Silver Woods, where a strange spell keeps them away from its heart, shifting them ever back to where they started. However, they can sense the presence of the elves, who ignore Lilith's calls for an alliance. Before the companions can ponder their next move, they are alerted by a scream.
3: The companions save an elf named Ariel, who guides them to a place of eternal night, the burial ground of the high elves. She awakens a great Elfward, and urges Stella to put her true power on display.

1: During the battle against Riel's guardian, the crew ends up surrounded by elven archers. However, Riel commands for them to stand down, revealing her true identity as Estariel, their leader. She leads them into the inner sanctuary, where the ancient dragon Rustamov bestows his mark to Light and perishes. Before they can dwell on the events, an uninvited hooded guest appears before them.
3: The fiend slips away as elven reinforcements arrive. With the barrier over the Silver Woods fading in the great dragon Rustamov's wake, Estariel announces that the elves will accept Lilith's proposed alliance. That evening, Estariel shares a tale of Starview's Keeper with Stella, and tests Lilith's resolve.

The crew and their new allies pause for a break on the way back to the Resistance's base. They eat elven pastries and listen to Light speak of Shakari's younger days, much to Lilith's delight. The revelry is cut short when they notice flames coming from the base's direction, which everyone hurries toward.

The party reach the base—or what's left of it. They learn that a desperate refugee sold them out to Commander Ilbis, who gleefully turns his new toy into a daemon. Ilbis then transforms himself and attacks.

1: Shakari senses something amiss after defeating Ilbis, and orders the survivors to run. With only seconds to react, the party find themselves face to face with the Lord of Shadow.
3: The Lord of Shadow rains destruction upon the Resistance base. Estariel flees, whisking the party away with her to regroup. They encounter Adjudicus, a fiend rebel who can sneak them into Excelion. Lilith argues that duty demands she stand and fight. Shakari knocks the girl out, and the party embark for the World Flipper.
4: The party slip into Excelion, and Lilith comes around, agreeing to open the passage to the World Flipper—only to find a gaping hole where it once stood. With the Lord of Shadow drawing nearer, Shakari sacrifices herself to buy Stella enough time to pry open a link to the fiends' world, Pandemonium.

1: A young diviner pursues a fox-eared girl through a twilit town. Just as they're gearing up to fight, however, the World Flipper launches Alk and the party right between them.
4: The diviner, Suizen, recognizes the party as interworld travelers. He introduces the world they've landed in as Yamato, and offers to lead them to the World Flipper.

3: Suizen explains that the ghostly foes they fought are "yokai," supernatural beings from an alternate Yamato in the West, which partially merged with its Eastern counterpart five years ago.

1: Suizen reveals he is Chair of the Diviners' Commission, which controls the World Flipper. To use it, the party must catch the fox girl, who may have info about the Yamatos' merge. They head to check a house she's been haunting.
Just as the party approach the house, they find a goblin heckling its owner, a samurai named Soushiro. The party jump in to save the seemingly unconcerned man from getting gobbled.
3: The goblin reverts into three fox kits who've been playfully pranking Soushiro. He calls for their friend, the fox girl Inaho, to come out. Seeing Stella close to him, however, Inaho declares her a rival and attacks.
5: Inaho runs away, vowing to get Soushiro next time. The party decide they aren't turning the lovestruck girl over to Suizen, but still want to talk with her. They head off to find Inaho with directions from Soushiro.

1: The long staircase takes a toll on the party, but Stella refuses to leave until she's spoken to Inaho about the Yamatos' merge. No sooner do they reach the top than they're turned away by an angry fox spirit.
3: Inaho shows up, and the fighting subsides. The fox spirit, Shirano, explains that the local "hauntings" are just Inaho trying (and failing) to confess to Soushiro, who arrives just in time to overhear.
4: Soushiro gently rejects Inaho, but she runs away crying—with Stella following after. Soushiro explains that Stella had a diviner's Shikigami stuck to her, but before they can warn her, Suizen appears and kidnaps Inaho.

1: The party fight their way past ninjas and arrive at the World Flipper, where Suizen is preparing to send Inaho back to her homeworld.
3: Defeated, Suizen puts up a barrier to buy time, and Inaho hurriedly bids farewell to Soushiro and her new friend Stella. Before Suizen can banish her, however, he is betrayed by his subordinate—who's in league with the masked sorceress!
5: While the party have their hands full fending off shadowy foes, the masked sorceress uses Inaho's power and the World Flipper to summon Orochi, a horrific eight-headed serpent. She then grabs Inaho and teleports away.
7: Suizen blames himself for unknowingly playing into the sorceress' plot. He asks to join the party—and has an idea of how they can stop Orochi.

3: The seal on Orochi had also been holding back countless yokai, who now stand between the serpent and the party. They're also attacked by ninjas, who Soushiro engages while the party hurry on to Orochi.

1: The sorceress explains her evil plans—merge all the worlds into one infinite realm of chaos. Suizen casts a dangerous spell to consume all the trapped yokai spirits powering Orochi. Knowing it will cost Suizen his life, Inaho and Stella try to break the spell while the others fight off daemons.
3: Stella and Inaho break Suizen's Circle of Corrosion, saving his life—and Orochi's. Soushiro gently scolds Suizen for his recklessness as the party gears up to take care of Orochi the old-fashioned way.
5: The sorceress revives Orochi with souls still trapped by the fractured seal. Suizen decides to break the seal completely, freeing all the souls. With no lives to fuel it, Orochi dissipates. In the scuffle, the sorceress' mask breaks—revealing a girl identical to Stella.
6: Orochi defeated and sorceress escaped, the party refocus on the World Flipper. Inaho's excited by the gateway to and from her homeworld, while Suizen is too busy handling Orochi's aftermath to stop her. Yamato conflicts resolved, the party strike out for the next world.

1: A lone android's reveries are interrupted when a UFO comes barreling down from space, setting off an alarm. She rushes towards the crash site, where Alk, Light, Stella, and Nimbus are facing off against malfunctioning cleaning bots.
3: After beating off the over-zealous mecha-janitors, Alk and co. meet the android singer Diva Media, better known as Dia. With the city out hunting for intruders, Dia offers to shelter the companions back at her house.

2: Alk and co. are enraptured by Dia's music, which rings out over the city. But the singer herself denounces the songs, calling them artificial. When Stella praises Dia's voice and expresses a wish to hear her live, a malfunctioning ticket machine leaps on the girl and knocks her unconscious.

1: When Stella awakens with a mysterious fever, Dia suggests that they seek help from her manager, Regis. After some wheedling from the pop star, Regis agrees take the fugitives to a place of safety.

The companions arrive at an abandoned city, where they meet hollows—droids who've had their minds wiped as punishment for committing a crime. Regis provides them relief by feeding them "memory bytes," an offense that soon attracts security. Ignoring Regis's appeals to hide, Alk and Nimbus leap out in defense of the poor, haunted hollows.
3: When a tenacious security bot launches itself at Dia, Regis is forced to save her—with the help of a hidden arm cannon. Though hurt that he's been keeping secrets from her, Dia convinces Regis to guide Alk and co. to the Cradle, where the World Flipper is deduced to be.

1: Past the Point of No Return - 1
2: Past the Point of No Return - 2

1: Noting that the bugs seem intent on eliminating Stella and Stella only, Regis questions her about her identity. Dia and the others rise up in her defense, but are soon interrupted by the arrival of new security forces.

Daunted by the wave after wave of security crashing upon them, Regis attempts to steal Dia away and abandon the Alk and co. to their fate. After reporting the companions' whereabouts, Regis promises a horrified Dia that he will protect her from the wrath of their overlord, the fearsome Administrator.
3: Alk and co. defeat Regis, just in time for a small bot controlled by the Administrator to arrive on the scene. Infuriated by Dia's loyalty to the intruders, the Administrator threatens to rain vengeance on their heads, before the bot is torn apart by Nimbus.

When the last of Stella's strength gives out, the companions are forced to seek shelter for the night, where Dia soothes the feverish girl with her music. The tender melody also attracts a strange bug, who beckons them towards the Cradle.

1: At long last, the companions reach the Cradle, only to be snared by the Administrator. Before the Administrator can deal the final blow, however, countless bugs swarm the scene, and one shows Dia a vision of his past. When the Administrator destroys the offender, fury grants Stella mysterious powers, allowing her to break free from the cage and communicate with the bugs. Seeing an opening, Regis charges in from the blue and begins a fresh assault on the Administrator.
3: Regis—who is, as it turns out, a double agent—explains that bugs are formed from wiped memories. He's long been looking for a way to use them to overthrow the Administrator, who sits in the Room of Idols, and claims that Stella's control over them is the key to victory.

1: When Alk and co. find the Room of Idols locked, Stella sets the bugs to work breaking down the door. However, she is quickly overwhelmed by their rage and pain. After Dia's song recalls Stella, the pop star realizes that her voice is only chance they have at restoring the Administrator's humanity.
3: Centuries of solitude have eaten too far into the Administrator's mind, and after the tyrant is defeated in battle, all Dia can do is sing a song to ease her passing. As a final gift, the Administrator gives Dia a code that will bring down the firewall on droid discs and allow for the restoring of wiped memories.
4: When Stella synchronizes with the World Flipper, it shows her and Light a vision of Starview from ages past. After a few encouraging words from Dia, the four world-hoppers part ways with the droids and continue their adventure.

1: After their underwater adventure, the party arrives in a dry canyon. Nimbus smells beasts in the area—or his stinky armpits? One of the two.
Nimbus sniffs out a pack of canid beastfolk, who mistake him for someone called Whitetail and attack. Whoever Whitetail is, he sure isn't popular!
3: Dogfolk defeated, the party wonder whether this beastfolk-filled canyon could be Nimbus's homeworld, and head towards a village for more information.

1: The party arrive in a town full of catfolk, who mob Nimbus, celebrating the return of "King Whitetail." Just as they're about to get an explanation from a panther named Claw, dogfolk strike again.
4: Chatty Claw tries to butter Nimbus up with compliments, but is cut off by a bomb-slinging boar-riding canid.
6: Canid cavalry subdued, Claw asks Nimbus to help put an end to the beastfolk's war—under the guise of his look-alike, Whitetail.

3: Claw explains that peace talks twenty years ago went awry when canid radicals assassinated King Whitetail and his infant son. Nimbus, pretending to be the lost prince, is to resume his "Father's" negotiations.

1: The party meet Claw's friend, a canid knight named Albert. He outlines the plan—Nimbus will meet with the king of dogfolk as "Prince Whitetail."
As they enter the canid castletown, the party get to know their new companions a little better—until a guard spots the feline visitors.
4: The party find themselves caught in the middle of a coup—with guards fighting both with and against them. They press on towards the throne room.

1: The party reach the king, to whom Claw eloquently introduces "Whitetail." They call for a ceasefire; the king calls for his dire wolf assassin, Klaus.
3: Defeated, the king appoints Albert his regent, giving him full-command of peace negotiations. The party start heading back to the catfolk village to seal the deal.
As the others sleep, Claw admits that he didn't REALLY think Nimbus was a long-lost prince—but their chance meeting finally made his dream of ending the war come true.

1: The catfolk chief is all too excited by news of the dogfolk coup's success—calling it a chance for the catfolk to strike! The only way to save the treaty is prove Whitetail's identity.

2: Claw leads the way to a charred graveyard, stopping by the ruins of what once was a holy sanctum. As Nimbus approaches, perplexed by a sense of familiarity, a door into the sanctum opens.

3: The sanctum appears a likely candidate for the World Flipper, but is guarded by King Whitetail's vengeful spirit.
5: Anger subdued, Whitetail leaves Nimbus a ring that unlocks the World Flipper, proving his identity. The catfolk replace their chief with Claw, who sees off the party as they depart for the next world.

1: It's another fine day on the ocean blue for the Crimson Blades, a pirate crew feared across all the seas, when a ragtag group of adventurers suddenly crash land on their deck. Mistaking them for stowaways, the pirate crew attacks—questions can come later, right?
3: The Crimson Blades have no interest in what Alk and the others have to say. Just when things start to seem hopeless, the crimson-haired captain of the crew makes a grand entrance and decides to hear them out. Regardless of the story, Alk and the others will have to earn their keep if they want to stay on board—as pirates.

1: Light and Nimbus have a hard time adapting to the salty sea air and battling seasickness. The pirates reveal to them that this world was submerged underwater long ago, and that Beastfolk like Nimbus also live here. The Crimson Blades are currently heading for the nearest landmass, known as a Float, while protecting a fleet of merchant ships.

The ship safely arrives at its destination, along with a fleet of merchant ships. Light attempts to part ways with the Crimson Blades, but with no destination and knowledge to navigate this new world, he reluctantly decides to join the pirates on their next voyage—to take out other pirates.

Light is curious as to why Marina has decided to hunt other pirate ships, despite being the captain of a pirate crew herself. She claims that having other pirates plaguing merchant ships in the area is bad for business. On top of that, she's gunning for whatever treasures they may have on board.
3: In celebration of her victory against the pirates, Marina pockets some treasure for herself. Some of the defeated pirates recognize her and the Crimson Blades, but have a hard time remembering her actual name.
5: Alk and the others investigate the cargo hold and find what appears to be a mermaid being held captive in a tank. In one swift blow, Marina breaks the mermaid free. She introduces herself as Amelia, and thanks the group before returning to the sea.

2: With their work finally behind them, Marina and the Crimson Blades join Alk and the others for a celebratory feast. Completely enamored by Alk's cooking prowess, Marina attempts to recruit him as a chef for the Crimson Blades, but Alk has no intention of ending his journey with Light and Stella yet.

1: Marina has prepared a submarine to explore the underwater ruins on the ocean floor that the mermaids have made their home. However, the campaign is cut short when a Kraken entangles their ship.

The crew manages to fight off the Kraken, but the damage to the keel has been done—the ship sinks to the bottom of the sea. When Light and the others come to, they find themselves somehow able to breathe in a world underwater.
Alk and the others reunite with Marina and the Crimson Blades, who have taken the opportunity to get their hands on all the treasure they can find under the sea.
While in search of the World Flipper, the group is confronted by an aggressive group of mermaids, who have mistaken them for being responsible for taking Amelia's life.
3: The misunderstanding is finally cleared up when Amelia shows up to stop the brawl. She reveals that she used her abilities to give Alk and the others the ability to breathe underwater. The mermaids agree to assist in the group's search for the World Flipper, when they're suddenly attacked.
5: Light is convinced that the monsters who have infested the sanctuary are not ordinary monsters, but daemons. Alk and the others let Amelia lead the way as they venture deeper into the sanctuary.

1: Is THAT How You Greet a Friend?

As the group ventures deeper into the mermaid's sanctuary, more and more daemons appear. When they encounter a giant crab, Amelia recognizes it as her friend Hermie. However, it ignores her greeting and attacks in a blind rage.

After quelling Hermie's rage, Alk and the others enter the inner sanctuary. The gorgeous ruins suggest that an advanced civilization once fluorished here. Upon seeing its current dilapidated state, Light dwells on how little he actually knows of his own world.

The group finally finds the treasure they were looking for—the World Flipper. However, the celebration is cut short when the masked sorceress makes an appearance. Although Marina isn't impressed by her antics, the sorceress summons a wave of daemons to attack.
3: Although the group manages to defeat her daemons, the masked sorceress taunts them once more before making an escape. When Stella activates the World Flipper this time, her body and Light's begin to glow. Despite Alk being left out of the phenomenon, he remains steadfast to see this journey through. Marina and the Crimson Blades leave for their next adventure, and Alk and co. take the plunge into a new world.

1: Alk, Light, and Stella descend into a world of endless sand and must face off against their most fearsome enemy yet: the climate.
When Alk and co. see a young boy facing off against a tiger-man many times his size, they step in on the side of the little one.
3: After driving off the tiger-man, Alk and co. win the trust the boy, Nadir, and strike out for his town.

Alk and co. receive an audience with the Lord of the Oasis, who rules Nadir's town. When the Lord has Nadir thrown into the dungeons for his failure to hunt down the beast, Alk offers to bring back the tiger-man in exchange for the boy's freedom.

1: The hunt for the tiger-man leads Alk, Light, and Stella to some old ruins. Instead of the beast, however, they find traces of an advanced civilization.
3: Alk and co. anger the guardian of the ruins and find themselves fighting for their lives.
5: In a last-ditch effort to eliminate Alk, Stella, and Light, the guardian sends out a power surge that brings the ruins crumbling down. The three struggle to the exit, only to find Nadir standing in their way. When the tiger-man appears, knocking Nadir out and saving all of their lives, Alk and co. decide to follow him back to village, sensing that there is more to his story.

1: In the Path of the Tiger - 1
2: In the Path of the Tiger - 2

1: Alk and co. arrive back at the town, just in time to save the tiger-man from being overwhelmed by a small army. The beast continues on to the throne room, seeking to avenge a dead friend.
4: The companions reach the throne room, only to find it empty. However, the tiger-man, who was friends with the previous Lord, Rolan, locates a secret passageway. They follow it to its end, where they discover the current Lord waiting for them in an ancient structure with a deadly surprise.
6: With the Custodian defeated, Alk and co. have to convince a furious beast not to spill the false Lord's blood. No sooner have they done so than a masked figure appears and erases the Lord from existence.
7: The companions discover the World Flipper in the depths of the structure and learn that Light's world is not in the region. Alk, Light, and Stella prepare to continue their adventure, but not before adding the tiger-man, Nimbus, to their party. Nadir arrives just in time to repair burnt bridges and part from Nimbus in friendship.

1: パルペブラ近郊にシブヤが現れてからしばらくして、リリス達の世界は限界が近づき粛清者が現れるようになっていた。そこでノヴァからの提案で粛清が始まる前に上位者を討とうと話し合っている所に、『グラム・ウォルンタス』なる人物から招待状が届く

3: 招待状に従い迷宮を訪れたアルク達は、差出人であるグラム・ウォルンタス、通称迷宮の魔術師と相対する。シブヤが混ざったことで、揺らぎが強まり続ける現状に苦悶するグラムに手を差し伸べたアルク達は、魔法学院長『ニルヤーナ・ウォルンタス』と出会う
かつてファーランドの魔導研究者であった二人の過去を聞いたアルク達は、揺らぎの迷宮誕生の経緯を知る。この世界に住む人々の『世界観』が揺らぎ、迷宮の孔も広がり続けている現状を打破するべく、スイゼンを筆頭とした星見の街の天才達が時間稼ぎに臨む

1: 招待状が届いたあの日から早半年が過ぎた頃、現実改変儀式機構『ランカ・ウォルンタス』を用いて迷宮の孔を塞いだアルク達。頼れる仲間達と分担して世界を救うべく行動を続けるアルク達は、ニルヤーナの依頼で粛清者の捕獲に挑む
3: ノヴァが槍を用いたことで犠牲者なく粛清者の捕獲に成功したアルク達。その夜、ノヴァ達と共に思い出のカレー屋を訪れたアルクは、将来への展望を語ったり親友と『いつも通り』生きて帰ることを誓ったりしながら、決戦の日に向けて準備を進めるのだった

1: 時が経ち何度目かの冬が訪れた頃、ステラ達と協力して粛清者から情報を引き出していたニルヤーナは、何者かの介入を受けて結界を破られてしまう。すると、突然街中に大量の抗体が現れアルクはパルペブラの人々を守るべく群れに突撃する
ニルヤーナの手により守護されていたステラ達の無事を確認したアルクは、ベルセティアと共に狭間の世界を経由して迷宮に転移する。転移した先で異形の粛清者と相対したアルク達は、危機を察知して迷宮に駆けつけていたエデュケウスと共に戦いに挑む
戦いの中で呪いに呑まれてしまったアルクは、優しい声に導かれて正気を取り戻すとエデュケウスと協力して異形の粛清者を撃破する。しかし、結界は完全に破壊されてしまい世界各地に粛清者が出現し、仲間達は協力して住民の避難や粛清者の対処に当たり始める
グラムの力によって地上に脱出したアルクは、街の崩壊を目の当たりにしてしまい悲嘆に叫ぶも、その場に居合わせたメムラムに背中を押されノヴァと共に駆けていく。一方、街中で住民の避難を支援していたナオ達は路地の先でレーヴェと倒れたサクヤを発見する
少人数でも上位者の元へ送り込み元凶を断つ作戦に切り替えようとしたアルク達だったが、頼みの綱のランカ・ウォルンタスは破壊されてしまっていた。しかし、グラムに助けを求めたニルヤーナの詠唱が始まり新たな希望の芽が芽吹こうとしていた
コード・ウォルンタス
グラムとニルヤーナが協力して発動した秘儀によってランカ・ウォルンタスに似た光の『発射台』が新たに生成される。身体を張って発射台を守るユキ達の姿を見て飛び出すのを我慢し続けるアルクの下に、シルティーを始めとしたパルペブラの仲間達が駆け付ける
3: 発射台を生成する力が足りず焦っていたノヴァ達の下に、サクヤをナオ達に託したレーヴェが飛び込んでくる。レーヴェの力も借りて完全に生成された光のランカ・ウォルンタスに乗り込み、ギリギリ合流したシロも伴ってアルク達は上位者の下へ飛び立つ

1: Nimbus manages to make an opening for the gang to escape from Shota and his new gravity powers. Retreating into the subway, Seiji recounts to the group how Ayumu, Shota, and Yuki met one another.
3: Nao is swallowed up by the Rift and starts to lose herself. Alk runs in after her to save her, reclaiming his memories in the process.
4: Alk dreams of the day he met Mikoto Hoshino. Coming back to reality, Alk wakes up in Starview and is told that Shibuya is running out of time. He hurries back to save his home city.

2: Yuki finds Alk and friends and tells them that Aegis plans to willingly walk into the Starsayers' trap in order to obtain the Dragon's Iris. The group quickly heads over to put a stop to the fighting.

1: Alk and company jump into the middle of the fighting between the Starsayers and Aegis. Nimbus and Yuki decide to hold off Ryuichi and Rinne, telling Alk and the others to go on ahead.
3: The One Who Has It All
Alk and Shota face off, letting out their grievances and inner feelings in the process. On the roof, Tohru and Sakuya get ready to fight one another.
With a little help from Yuki, Alk takes down Tohru. However, Leve appears and activates the Dragon's Iris, summoning a strange Purger to attack.

2: When It Comes Time to Wake
Betraying Leve, Sakuya begins the process of destroying the world. Elsewhere, Seiji finds Shota staring dejectedly at the sky.
3: Not giving up on the crumbling world, Alk and Shota knock the Dragon's Iris out of the sky. Just as Stella attempts to stitch the world back together, a beast appears from the Iris, prompting the start of the final battle.

1: Despite the defeat of the Dragon's Iris, the world continues to crumble. After sending their friends to gather people and bring them to safety, Stella and Alk decide to save everyone by doing the wrong thing.
2: Alk and Stella save Leve, who in turn helps them save Sakuya. With the power of the Antipode Lance, Shibuya merges with the world of Palpebra. In the aftermath, Alk speaks with Leve in the Rift before Nova finds him and brings him home.
3: Palpebra scrambles to deal with the addition of Shibuya to their world. Yuki and Shota decide on new paths in life, while Alk and friends prepare for their next battle.

1: Attempting to cross the Rift to another world, Alk wakes up alone and in a familiar place.
In the ruins of Shibuya Station, Alk defends two strangers from a teenager summoning dragonlings.
3: After reuniting with Nimbus, Alk learns that the two strangers are Yuki and Shota, who know him as a person named Ayumu.

1: Unsure how to act with people who apparently know him, Alk follows Shota and Yuki to the emergency shelter run by the Starsayers. There, he meets Nao, who is evidently his little sister.
2: Alk and co. gather information about what has happened to Shibuya. Their info session is interrupted by an attack from Aegis, an organization of people who possess supernatural powers.

1: Alk and Stella successfully fend off the members of Aegis and are invited to meet Sakuya Hoshino, the leader of the Starsayers. After exchanging information, Alk and Stella leave without forging an alliance.
2: Alk, feeling that Sakuya is untrustworthy, decides to meet with Aegis. Yuki, who has secretly possessed powers this whole time, offers to show them the way.

1: The gang arrive at Aegis' base, but a familiar angry teen blocks their way and begins a battle.
3: After trading information with Tohru Sengaku, Aegis' powerful leader, the group heads to the Shibuya River.
While Alk and co. search the river, they notice that the underground passage smells too clean. Suddenly, a monster that looks like the goddess Benten appears and attacks.

2: Discovering countless unconscious bodies in the river's drainage area, the gang enter battle with the Starsayers' members guarding the area.

1: Nova warns the group that Stella and the others are in trouble at the emergency shelter. Hurrying over and meeting up, Alk and co. are stopped by Shota, who airs grievances and prepares to fight them.

The World Flipper launches Alk and company to a verdant forest, rich in flora. However, the scenery is unfamiliar to Light, who doesn't recognize this world as his own. They don't have much time to dwell on it, however, as a monster strikes from the shrubbery.
3: Lost in the woods, the party begins searching for their key to another world—the World Flipper. According to Stella, all worlds contain one. Before they can begin their search, however, Stella gets distracted by a strange mushroom creature.

1: The group follows the mushroom creature and finds it surrounded by monsters. Alk and Light leap into action to save it from danger.

The mushroom's name is Shroombo, a forest sprite in search of his friend, Challua. When the group finds Challua, her body appears to be withered and lifeless, but with a little water and sunlight, she's good as new. The friendly reunion is cut short when another monster strikes from the skies.
3: Alk is about to finish the owl monster off when Challua stops him, claiming that he's a friend. She leads the group to find refuge in a grove, where they set up camp for the night. When Challua reveals that she plans on going to the Spirit Tree to find someone, the group decides to accompany her.

1: When the group makes it to the Spirit Tree, Light senses a mysterious miasma eminating from it. Alk and the others brace themselves for whatever awaits them inside.

As suspected, the World Flipper is discovered inside the Spirit Tree. However, before Alk can get near its flippers, roots sprout from beneath the ground, attacking him. Challua manages to save him, but the miasma continues to grow even stronger as another monster attacks.
Before the group can catch their breath after taking out the tree monster, the cause of the miasma appears before them—Regitare, the Undead Lord.
3: Try as they might, Alk and the others cannot seem to keep Regitare subdued. But when Stella activates the World Flipper, he regains his senses and stops his onslaught—much to Challua's pleasure. With the World Flipper activated, Stella is able to access this world's coordinates for future travel.
4: Regitare explains that he had no control over his actions after touching the corrupted World Flipper. Light considers the relation between this and his battle with the Lord of Shadow. Unfortunately, it appears that his homeworld is still nowhere in sight. Challua and Stella make a promise to see each other again, and the group plunges into their next destination.
